questions.questionText: A small block of mass 100g is tied to a spring of spring constant 7.5 N/m and length 20 cm. The other end of spring is fixed at a particular point A. questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: The Kinetic energy of an electron, α–particle and a proton are given as 4K, 2K and K respectively. The de–Broglie wavelength associated with electron (λₑ), α–particle (λα) and the proton (λₚ) are as follows:
questions.concept: Wavelength dependence on kinetic energy and mass

questions.concept: Weight on different planets with same density

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText:
Given below are two statements: one is labelled as Assertion A and the other is labelled as Reason R.
Assertion A: Earth has atmosphere whereas moon doesn't have any atmosphere.
Reason R: The escape velocity on moon is very small as compared to that on earth.
In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below:

options.text: Both A and R are correct and R is the correct explanation of A
A is true but R is false
Both A and R are correct but R is NOT the correct explanation of A
A is false but R is true

questions.concept: Atmospheric retention and escape velocity

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: A long straight wire of circular cross-section (radius a) is carrying steady current I. The current I is uniformly distributed across this cross-section. The magnetic field is

options.text: directly proportional to r in the region r < a and inversely proportional to r in the region r > a
inversely proportional to r in the region r < a and uniform throughout in the region r > a
uniform in the region r < a and inversely proportional to distance r from the axis, in the region r > a
zero in the region r < a and inversely proportional to r in the region r > a

questions.concept: Ampere's law for cylindrical conductor

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: A monochromatic light wave with wavelength λ₁ and frequency v₁ in air enters another medium. If the angle of incidence and angle of refraction at the interface are 45° and 30° respectively, then the wavelength λ₂ and frequency v₂ of the refracted wave are:
questions.concept: Wavelength and frequency change during refraction

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText:
Given below are two statements: one is labelled as Assertion A and the other is labelled as Reason R.
Assertion A: When a body is projected at an angle 45°, its range is maximum.
Reason R: For maximum range, the value of sin 2θ should be equal to one.
In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below:

options.text: A is true but R is false
Both A and R are correct but R is NOT the correct explanation of A
Both A and R are correct and R is the correct explanation of A
A is false but R is true

questions.concept: Maximum range condition in projectile motion

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText:
The induced emf can be produced in a coil by
A. moving the coil with uniform speed inside uniform magnetic field
B. moving the coil with non-uniform speed inside uniform magnetic field
C. rotating the coil inside the uniform magnetic field
D. changing the area of the coil inside the uniform magnetic field
Choose the correct answer from the options given below:
questions.concept: Conditions for electromagnetic induction

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: A steel rod has a radius of 20 mm and a length of 2.0 m. A force of 62.8 kN stretches it along its length. Young's modulus of steel is 2.0 ×10¹¹ N/m². The longitudinal strain produced in the wire is _____×10⁻⁵
questions.concept: Strain calculation using Young's modulus

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: An ideal transformer with purely resistive load operates at 12 kV on the primary side. It supplies electrical energy to a number of nearby houses at 120 V. The average rate of energy consumption in the houses served by the transformer is 60 kW. The value of resistive load (Rs) required in the secondary circuit will be ____________ Ω.
questions.concept: Power and resistance in transformer circuits

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: The length of a metallic wire is increased by 20% and its area of cross section is reduced by 4%. The percentage change in resistance of the metallic wire is _____________.
questions.concept: Effect of dimensional changes on resistance

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: A parallel plate capacitor with plate area A and plate separation d is filled with a dielectric material of dielectric constant K = 4. The thickness of the dielectric material is x, where x < d. Let C₁ and C₂ be the capacitance of the system for X = d/3 and X = 2d/3, respectively. If C₁ = 2μF the value of C₂ is ___________ μF.
questions.concept: Capacitance calculation with partial dielectric filling

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: The radius of fifth orbit of the Li²⁺ is _____________ × 10⁻¹²m. Take: radius of hydrogen atom = 0.51 Å.
questions.concept: Orbital radius calculation for hydrogen-like ions

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: A pole is vertically submerged in swimming pool, such that it gives a length of shadow 2.15 m within water when sunlight is incident at an angle of 30° with the surface of water. If swimming pool is filled to a height of 1.5 m, then the height of the pole above the water surface in centimetres is (nw = 4/3).

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: Two identical circular wires of radius 20 cm and carrying current √2 A are placed in perpendicular planes as shown in figure. The net magnetic field at the centre of the circular wires is _________ × 10⁻⁸ T. (Take π = 3.14)
questions.concept: Superposition of magnetic fields from perpendicular current loops

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: Two identical solid spheres each of mass 2 kg and radii 10 cm are fixed at the ends of a light rod. The separation between the centres of the spheres is 40 cm. The moment of inertia of the system about an axis perpendicular to the rod passing through its middle point is ___________ × 10⁻³ kg-m²
questions.concept: Moment of inertia of system of spheres using parallel axis theorem

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: A particle of mass 10 g moves in a straight line with retardation 2x, where x is the displacement in SI units. Its loss of kinetic energy for above displacement is (x/10)ⁿ J. The value of n will be ________.
questions.concept: Work done against variable retarding force

questions.subject: PHYSICS
questions.questionText: A person driving car at a constant speed of 15 m/s is approaching a vertical wall. The person notices a change of 40Hz in the frequency of his car's horn upon reflection from the wall. The frequency of horn is ________Hz. (Given: Speed of sound : 330 m/s)
questions.concept: Doppler effect for sound reflection from a wall
